==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/tiːt/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːt|-iːt]]

===Etymology===
French ''[[tette]]'', which is of Teutonic origin and replaced Old English ''[[titt]]'', which survives as English ''[[tit]]''. Confer German ''[[Zitze]]'', "teat".

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# the [[projection]] of a [[mammary gland]] from which, on [[female]] [[mammal]]s, [[milk]] is [[secrete]]d
# an [[artificial]] [[nipple]] used for [[bottle-feed]]ing [[infants]]

=====Synonyms=====
#[[nipple]], [[tit]]
#[[nipple]]

